SIMPLE: sylvan
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sylvan
<hw>Syl"van</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Silvan</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to a sylva;
forestlike; hence, rural; rustic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The traditional memory of a rural and a <qex>sylvan</qex> region .
. . is usually exact as well as tenacious.</q> <rj><qau>De
Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Abounding in forests or in trees; woody.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sylvan</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sylvan
<hw>Syl"van</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>Sylvanus</ets>, better
<ets>Silvanus</ets>. See <er>Silvan</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>A
fabled deity of the wood; a satyr; a faun; sometimes, a
rustic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her private orchards, walled on every side,⟦br⟧
To lawless <qex>sylvans</qex> all access denied.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sylvan</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Sylvan
<hw>Syl"van</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Sylva</ets> +
furfur<ets>an</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A liquid hydrocarbon
obtained together with furfuran (tetrol) by the distillation of pine
wood; -- called also <altname>methyl tetrol</altname>, or
<altname>methyl furfuran</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sylvanite</ent>⟦br⟧
